SIMPLE: landfall
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Landfall
<hw>Land"fall</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sudden
transference of property in land by the death of its owner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Sighting or making land when at
sea.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>A good landfall</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>the
sighting of land in conformity with the navigator's reckoning and
expectation.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Landflood</ent>⟦br⟧
